DERIVATION OF THE EFFECTIVE GROWTH EQUATION
for the curvature–memory field with interaction b T M^2
==============================================================

Goal
-----

Reduce the coupled system

    { δM , Φ , δ_b }

to a single approximate growth equation

    δ̈_b + 2H δ̇_b = 4π G_eff(a,k) ρ̄_b δ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
1. SUBHORIZON QUASI-STATIC REGIME
--------------------------------------------------------------

    k^2 / A^2  >>  H^2

    Φ̇ ≈ 0
    Ψ̇ ≈ 0
    Φ = Ψ


--------------------------------------------------------------
2. LINEAR MEMORY-FIELD EQUATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    δM̈ + 3H δṀ
    + (k^2/A^2 + 3a M̄^2 + 2b ρ̄_b) δM

    = - 2 b M̄ δρ_b
      - (2a M̄^3 + 2b ρ̄_b M̄) Ψ

    m_eff^2 = 3a M̄^2 + 2b ρ̄_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
3. SOLVING FOR δM
--------------------------------------------------------------

    δM ≈ - 2 b M̄ δρ_b / (k^2/A^2 + m_eff^2)


--------------------------------------------------------------
4. MEMORY-FIELD DENSITY PERTURBATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    δρ_M ≈ (a M̄^3 + 2b ρ̄_b M̄) δM + b M̄^2 δρ_b

    δρ_M = β(k,a) δρ_b

    β(k,a)
      = b M̄^2
        - 2 b M̄ (a M̄^3 + 2b ρ̄_b M̄)
          /(k^2/A^2 + m_eff^2)


--------------------------------------------------------------
5. MODIFIED POISSON EQUATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    (k^2/A^2) Φ = 4πG (1 + β) δρ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
6. EFFECTIVE NEWTON CONSTANT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    G_eff = G (1 + β)


--------------------------------------------------------------
7. FINAL BARYON GROWTH EQUATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    δ̈_b + 2H δ̇_b
      = 4π G_eff ρ̄_b δ_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
8. RESULT
--------------------------------------------------------------

    G_eff(k,a) = G [1 + β(k,a)]

    β(k,a)
      = b M̄^2
        - 2 b M̄ (a M̄^3 + 2b ρ̄_b M̄)
          /(k^2/A^2 + m_eff^2)

    m_eff^2 = 3a M̄^2 + 2b ρ̄_b


--------------------------------------------------------------
9. PHYSICAL INTERPRETATION
--------------------------------------------------------------

    • direct density tracking:   b M̄^2 δρ_b

    • scalar response:           δM ∝ δρ_b /(k^2/A^2 + m_eff^2)

    → Yukawa-like scale dependence


--------------------------------------------------------------
10. LIMITING REGIMES
--------------------------------------------------------------

Small scales:

    k^2/A^2 >> m_eff^2

    β ≈ b M̄^2

    G_eff ≈ G (1 + b M̄^2)

Large scales:

    k^2/A^2 << m_eff^2

    β ≈ b M̄^2
        - 2 b M̄ (a M̄^3 + 2b ρ̄_b M̄) / m_eff^2


--------------------------------------------------------------
11. CONNECTION TO S8
--------------------------------------------------------------

If

    b M̄^2 < 0

then

    G_eff < G

→ suppressed clustering


--------------------------------------------------------------
12. TESTABLE PREDICTIONS
--------------------------------------------------------------

    • fσ8(z)

    • G_eff(k,a)

    • redshift evolution via M̄(t)

    • comparison with DESI, Gold-2017, weak lensing


